<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>First</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, there may be location dependent bugs or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;features&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that disallow or instantly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;poof&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pets summoned in those location.  If this is the case, then those who cannot summon pets should be able to move to a new location and summon one.  As many pet poof bugs involve walls or zone boundaries, moving away from those might be best.  That said, I have summoned a pet near the wall by the bank near the exit to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Nexus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
